&lt;h1&gt;Who we are&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses and organizations. Millions of people - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups and now key public institutions - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and intelligently manage funds. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creating long-term value for our users is central to our mission at Stripe. The GTM Industries team focuses on long-term growth and value creation for enterprise customers and for Stripe, by understanding the unique challenges they face in their industry and how to solve them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We focus on building Stripe&#39;s expertise within key business verticals while delivering credibility and thought leadership needed to build relationships with industry leaders to grow the value of their business. Aligned with our GTM and Product teams, the Industry Strategist also defines relevant, value-centric solutions, supports our users, and generates new sources of value for users and Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team provides deep industry expertise across Stripe and leads enterprise business development, partnering with some of our most exciting enterprise and large SaaS platform users to address their business challenges and help them grow with Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Public Sector Industry Strategist, you will uncover growth opportunities and make informed recommendations. You will drive the development of strategic partnership development and GTM plays tailored to high-potential use cases, ensuring that our cross-functional teams are equipped to replicate successful motions. In collaboration with product and GTM teams, you will refine our value propositions to resonate with target markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct deep market research and analysis on Public Sector (Governments, Universities, School Districts, Utilities, and more) to identify trends, opportunities, and potential obstacles. Understand competitive landscapes to position Stripe effectively within industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity Identification: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define key use cases that present significant growth opportunities. Develop data-driven insights to inform business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GTM Play Development: &lt;/strong&gt;Create, iterate, and implement go-to-market plays for identified use cases. Ensure account teams have actionable insights and templates to engage prospects effectively and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quick Win Identification:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify opportunities for quick wins that can drive near-term revenue growth. Develop strategies to capitalize on these opportunities swiftly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thought Leadership: &lt;/strong&gt;Produce thought leadership content, such as whitepapers and case studies, highlighting Stripe&#39;s expertise within emerging industry verticals. Share insights with internal teams and prospects to bolster credibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; Build relationships with GTM leaders and key stakeholders. Act as a strategic advisor, helping them understand how Stripe&#39;s solutions can address their specific business challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Metrics: &lt;/strong&gt;Establish KPIs to evaluate the effectiveness of sales plays and industry strategies. Continuously analyze performance and iterate based on feedback and results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Work closely with Product, Marketing, and Sales teams to align strategies and ensure a cohesive approach to go-to-market initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training &amp;amp; Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide training and support to account teams on new plays and industry-specific insights. Ensure they are well-equipped to articulate the value of Stripe&#39;s solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feedback Loop: &lt;/strong&gt;Collect user and market feedback on our solutions to inform product development and strategy adjustments, ensuring we stay ahead of industry needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Industry Strategist will be a seasoned professional with extensive experience in business strategy, industry analysis, and go-to-market execution. You are an expert in Public Sector and have a proven track record of working in or with that sector. You possess a deep understanding of the unique challenges and opportunities that governments and other public sector organizations face.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You excel at engaging in high-level business discussions as well as detailed technical conversations across various roles within an organization. Your expertise in solution definition and value proposition crafting allows you to articulate complex strategies in a clear and compelling manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a strategic thinker with strong analytical skills, demonstrating an ability to distill industry insights into actionable strategies. Your excellent communication skills enable you to connect effectively with diverse audiences, from clients to internal stakeholders, including executives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thriving in competitive environments, you are adept at building value propositions that resonate with target markets. You are equally comfortable working independently as you are in collaborative team settings, contributing your knowledge and insights to drive collective success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an organized self-starter who enjoys diving deep into data and trends to identify growth opportunities. With a track record of improving processes and enhancing organizational effectiveness, you are proactive in making things happen and achieving results. Your passion for becoming an industry expert motivates you to continuously learn and share your knowledge with others, helping to elevate the entire organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;11+ years experience in public sector, technology, or payments industry roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in public sector industry strategy, business development, or related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand complex technical requirements and craft solutions across multiple stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in defining user needs and translating those needs into solutions and strategies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with enterprise SaaS or financial infrastructure markets is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills, including presentation skills, particularly for in-person meetings with multiple stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem solving skills, including the ability to derive actionable insights from large amounts of information and clearly articulate complex ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to build strong collaborative working relationships and influence outcomes with business partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to be a self-starter capable of driving business results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An enthusiastic “roll up your sleeves” mentality and thrive in a fast-moving environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel up to 20% to industry events, Stripe-led events or key customer meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payments and/or Enterprise Software industry experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a top-tier management consulting firm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience growing a high growth industry-focused team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working on or with Sales teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s global demand campaigns team delivers marketing campaigns that drive awareness and engagement for our audiences, solutions, and products worldwide. Working closely with sales and marketing teams, our campaigns support Stripe’s larger business objectives and deliver impact. We build, deliver, monitor, and evolve campaign delivery across a broad suite of content, tactics, and channels. Using a broad suite of metrics, we continuously measure our work and refine our strategies to improve outreach, enhance the customer journey, and support revenue growth for the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you’ll champion an audience or solution, and you’ll quarterback the integrated campaign plans and playbooks for that focus area in alignment with regional GTM strategies. You’ll be an expert in your focus area, holding deep market and audience insight and direct business accountability. You’ll lead a large, global, cross-functional workstream to build campaign strategies and content, then work with regional teams to deliver materials through integrated channels. You’ll capture performance against all of your efforts, analyze results, and share learnings to drive continuous improvement and impact. Ultimately, you’ll be accountable for acquisition, engagement, and pipeline growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excels in leading and driving large, complex, global campaigns or programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has strong analytics skills, with the ability to interpret, analyze, and communicate campaign performance across marketing and sales KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with and influences across cross-functional stakeholder groups, including senior sales, marketing, and product leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has a proven track record developing global campaigns and delivering campaign playbooks for international localisation and execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is a passionate advocate for their users/audiences/customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Sees around corners”; anticipates and unblocks challenges, stays ahead of market/audience trends, and anticipates regional/country needs and nuance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands modern storytelling and content trends, and can translate those into thoughtful, resonant campaign strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is agile, iterative, AI-fluent, and comfortable with ambiguity and high growth environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the overall campaign strategy and plan for your audience or product, and drive the global, cross-functional workstream for activation and impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with comms, product marketing, channel teams, regional and field marketing, partner marketing, sales teams, and more to define and implement campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with regional marketing to ensure local relevance and advise on campaign delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use your multi-channel expertise to deliver campaigns via digital, web, email, online events, direct mail, social, events, sales plays, and more, all in partnership with functional and regional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product marketing and content/editorial teams to develop compelling, relevant campaign materials and content sets, including whitepapers, guides, blogs, checklists, interactive content, promotions/offers, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and/or recommend leading tools to improve or accelerate the work of the campaigns function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an expert for your owned audience/solution to champion market trends, competitive context, and customer insights, ultimately shaping all industry campaign strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track, analyze, and report on campaign performance metrics with a focus on lead generation, pipeline, and target account penetration. Share learnings regularly to improve overall campaign efficacy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of enterprise B2B marketing experience that includes some mix of integrated campaigns, content marketing, regional/field marketing, and/or account-based marketing, with demonstrated increase in scope&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional knowledge of FinTech industry landscape, trends, and technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in partnering with regional marketing and sales teams to build, grow, and develop pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical acumen, with the ability to build, interpret, and adjust measurement tools and data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional presentation, writing, and communication skills, especially to executive stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Appetite and ability to work through ambiguity, evaluate and recommend solutions, and drive clarity across complex, global stakeholder groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build campaigns and programs from the ground, orchestrating many moving parts across disparate functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at a highly dynamic, fast-growing growth tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the payments, financial technology, or adjacent industries or marketing FinTech solutions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrated campaigns experience focused on select audiences: enterprise and industries (retail, media/entertainment/gaming, financial services, insurance, travel/hospitality/leisure), SMB/mid-market, SaaS platforms, startups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product campaigns experience focused on payments, fraud, financial services, and/or embedded finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Getting our users live and successful on Stripe is paramount to realizing our mission. We’re building a Launch function to help our users on their journey. The team will be at the forefront of driving growth – analyzing what’s working well that we want to replicate, figuring out where people might be getting stuck, designing automated and targeted journeys for all users, funneling more users to Partners and ProServ, and building out a multi-faceted team of user content creators, data analysts, program managers, integration engineers, and launch managers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Implementation Consultant on the Launch team, you&#39;ll own the relationships with our customers and be responsible for guiding them to successful Stripe implementations. Working closely with our Accelerate, ProServ, and Alliances and Channels Partners you&#39;ll proactively engage users and shepherd them through the integration process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the deal-signed-not-live backlog for users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closely partner with our SA manager team to ensure signed users have the right level of implementation offering attached, including for services from Professional Services or Partner teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intervene with stuck users to quickly unblock them, or route more complex requirements to other Implementation paths such as Accelerate, Product, Partner, or ProServ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unblock and enable users by facilitating internal Stripe processes and managing Stripe-owned tasks on their behalf.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On user-led implementations ensure handoff to Paid Support, Data Migrations, and other Stripe teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measuring and reporting on the progress and completion of user implementations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corporate internship or 2-5 years of relevant professional experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a customer-facing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, quantitative and operational capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort in operating in a highly ambiguous and fast paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating on multiple projects or initiatives simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc or equivalent degree in a related field (technology, business administration, project management etc,)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical aptitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management training or certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payments/ ecommerce experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a Professional Services organization or in a customer success/support organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A familiarity with APIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll be reporting into the New Hire Program Team, a sub-team under the Talent &amp;amp; Development function. This team delivers global Stripe wide onboarding and employee engagement programs for new hires and existing Stripes. We partner closely with the business and partner teams to support new managers and leaders in successfully integrating into Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to building an inclusive work environment where all Stripes feel welcomed as their authentic selves—inclusive of all genders, sexual orientations, ethnicities, races, education, ages, and other personal characteristics. We work on broadening our internal diversity because we want to be culturally equipped to build products and solutions for our diverse user base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Leadership Onboarding Partner, you will own the end-to-end strategy, design, and execution of our Manager Onboarding program and play a key role in our Leadership Onboarding strategy. This role requires a dynamic blend of expert facilitation for senior audiences, learning content design, and meticulous program management to ensure flawless delivery. You will partner closely with stakeholders across the organization to continuously iterate on program outcomes, setting up our new leaders for success in a high-impact, fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the design, delivery and operations of Manager Onboarding, partnering closely with subject matter experts to align with organizational needs and the company&#39;s latest strategic direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update program content across various modalities (live sessions, e-learning, webpages, and demos) in collaboration with internal and external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure lifecycle continuity by collaborating with the Manager Development team to align strategy and insights from onboarding through continuous leadership development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement by evaluating facilitated sessions and program strategy through participant feedback and assessment metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement strategic improvements, designing end-to-end onboarding experiences with rigorous operational planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design and execution of our Leadership Onboarding program in partnership with Head of Onboarding, Leadership Recruiting and People Partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilitation Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver expert facilitation for small and large group onboarding experiences, applying best-in-class adult learning design principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Host in-person bi-weekly Manager Onboarding sessions located in our San Francisco office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct impactful 360 feedback sessions to significantly enhance the effectiveness of leaders and their teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead engaging team dynamics sessions for leadership groups, cultivating stronger collaboration and business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support company-wide onboarding programs as an occasional facilitator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of program operations, maximizing efficiency and effectiveness while partnering with coordinators to streamline all logistical processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate strategically with stakeholders (People Partners, Hiring Managers, ABPs) across the organization to tailor onboarding experiences and iterate on program delivery models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize insights and feedback mechanisms to continuously refine and elevate onboarding outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional experience facilitating live sessions to audiences of high seniority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of program management experience for global programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of adult learning principles and how to apply them in a facilitation to senior audience context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive instructional design experience, building and iterating content in support of business goals with a strong eye for aesthetic design and branding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to drive complex, cross-functional projects from initial design to execution and evaluation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meticulous attention to detail and quality in support of effective, flawless delivery of content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing global partners and stakeholders to scale program deliveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with a talent for making complex concepts simple&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills, capable of working with cross-functional teams and managing stakeholder expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, self-directed, and performance-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build and maintain trusting relationships with business leaders and key partners across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional interpersonal skills: demonstrates effective listening, user needs assessment skills with the ability to synthesize data collected and identify the root problem causes and drive resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to make judgment calls and sound decisions, demonstrating strong accountability, confidentiality and professionalism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;People management experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Product Accounting: The Stripe Product Accounting Team is responsible for supporting all products at Stripe, consulting on accounting implications and supporting teams&#39; ability to make informed strategic decisions. We are responsible for the accurate and timely recording of all business-generated transactions on our balance sheet and income statement. We operate in a fast-paced environment and collaborate significantly with cross-functional and international teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is seeking an experienced accountant with an aptitude for data analysis to join its world class Accounting team and help us scale for the future, in a fast-paced environment that’s growing rapidly. As a member of the Product Accounting team, you will support the processing and reporting of our financial results for our transaction losses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with our risk management, data science and finance partners to thoroughly understand Stripe’s credit and fraud risk, and advise on accounting implications grounded in US GAAP guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, produce, and review monthly and quarterly close activities, including balance sheet reconciliations, reserve rollforwards, variance analysis and analytical reviews, producing internal management reporting and external audit support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable timely financial close and margin analysis through data analytics and visualization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrangle large, highly complex datasets into actionable insights and become a data expert for losses accounting. Perform analysis, identify trends, conduct research, and build visualizations to deliver objective, critical insights that fulfill accounting and finance stakeholders’ needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
